<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:401287F6FFDE0E6DFF5802EDFAC3F9AA:CD64603BFFDE0E6FFC4B076EFBCAF810" box="[923,1041,1908,1934]" country="Somalia" county="This" municipality="Miocene" name="According" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">According</location>
to 
<bibRefCitation author="Abbate, E. &amp; Sagri, M. &amp; Sassi, F. P." box="[1071,1291,1908,1935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" refId="ref2966" refString="Abbate, E., Sagri, M. &amp; Sassi, F. P. (Eds.) (1994) Geological map of Somalia. Scale 1: 1.500.000. Somali National University and Ministry of mineral and water resources, Mogadishu. Available from: https: // som-mine. com / smlive / wp-content / uploads / somali-geologicalmap. jpg (Accessed 15 December 2021)" type="url" year="1994">
Abbate 
<emphasis box="[1157,1204,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">et al</emphasis>
. (1994)
</bibRefCitation>
the geological substrate east of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:401287F6FFDE0E6DFF5802EDFAC3F9AA:CD64603BFFDE0E6FFE960782FE77F82D" box="[326,428,1944,1971]" country="Somalia" county="This" municipality="Miocene" name="Eyl town" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Eyl town</location>
is characterized by the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:401287F6FFDE0E6DFF5802EDFAC3F9AA:CD64603BFFDE0E6FFD690782FD24F82C" box="[697,767,1944,1970]" country="Somalia" county="This" municipality="Miocene" name="Hafun" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Hafun</location>
(Xaafuun) succession composed of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1178,1276,1944,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Miocene</collectingMunicipality>
biogenic reefal limestones. 
<collectingCounty box="[269,319,1980,2006]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">This</collectingCounty>
formation is widespread in 
<collectingCountry box="[633,725,1980,2006]" name="Somalia" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Somalia</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[779,894,1980,2006]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis box="[779,894,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">B. eilensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
potentially has a wider distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1044,2078]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,2016,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet ‘ 
<emphasis box="[604,697,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">eilensis’</emphasis>
refers to the town of Eyl where this new 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1397,2016,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis box="[1197,1306,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Blepharis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6359303" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6359303" box="[136,994,1596,1618]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6359303/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" startId="2.[136,229,1596,1618]" targetBox="[340,1247,190,1572]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,994,1596,1618]" box="[136,994,1596,1618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,254,1596,1618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baldesi &amp; Vollesen" authorityYear="2022" box="[259,431,1596,1617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Blepharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eilensis">
<emphasis box="[259,431,1596,1617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="64">Blepharis eilensis</emphasis>
